The paper deals with automated plant disease detection and diagnosis using computer vision techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of developing such systems, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG) techniques. The authors also mention the use of deep learning models, which is a popular topic in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of performance metrics, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
